personalInfo.education: Georgia State University; Wallace State Community College (2002)

tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt - Finished 11-45 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament (exempt to second reshuffle)
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Played in six events on the Mackenzie Tour - PGA TOUR Canada.



2013: Successfully defended his Georgia Open title.



2012: Won the Georgia Open.

 2008: Made 28 starts, making seven cuts. Had two top-10s, with a T3 at the Xerox Classic his best, playing in the final group Sunday. His other top 10 (T8) came at the Utah Championship. It included a hole-in-one at the seventh hole in the first round, one of a record four aces that day (others were Peter Tomasulo, Brian Stuard and Chris Stroud). Finished the season 93rd in earnings.

 2007: Winner of the Stonebridge Classic on the eGolf Tour, firing a final-round, 5-under 67 to overcome a one-stroke deficit at the beginning of the day to future PGA TOUR member Tommy Gainey.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: An Atlantic Sun Conference first-team all-conference selection, he became the first player in school history to earn full status on the Web.com Tour...Winner of the Sportsmanship Award at Georgia State University.
tourBios.personal: One of five siblings; brother, Cole, is a master sergeant in the U.S. Air Force...Grandfather was a champion professional boxer...Attended South Gwinnett High School in Snellville, Ga...Was 2004 Academic All-Conference in college...Earliest golf memory was playing the "Fricke Open" with father and brother the Friday after Thanksgiving...Father caddied for him when he won the 2012 Georgia Open...Biggest thrill outside golf was seeing his father beat cancer...If not a professional golfer, would be doing something in Major League Baseball...Would choose "Rain When I Die" by Alice in Chains if he had an entrance song at the first tee...Favorite courses played are Winged Foot GC, Mountain Top GC and Kinloch GC...Superstition is using quarters for ball marks with his little sisters' years of birth...Favorite teams are the University of Georgia and the Atlanta Braves...Favorite apps are Meme Maker, V1 Golf and Shazam...Favorite athletes are Chipper Jones, John Smoltz and Kris Medlan...Favorite TV shows are "Criminal Minds" and "NCIS."...Favorite movies are "Zero Dark Thirty," "Act of Valor" and "The Count of Monte Cristo."...Favorite vacation spot/cities are Charleston and Hilton Head Island, S.C...Would like to trade places with Frank Wren or Fredi Gonzalez "to make decisions for the Braves." ...Not many people know he loves music and tried to teach himself how to play the guitar, which is still on his bucket list...Supports charity Operation One Voice...Would like to be in Sports Illustrated, which would "mean I've done something great in golf."...First-tee introduction song would be "Rain When I Did" by Alice In Chains...Lists his first professional win on the Tarheel Tour as his biggest thrill in golf. In that tournament, his dadâwho had just finished chemotherapy treatments for cancerâwas his caddie...Twitter name is @jfrickegolf.
